Enterprise AWS Disaster Recovery Operations Manual
Part 1 – Introduction, Architecture, Recovery Strategy, Roles & Responsibilities, and DR Readiness Validation
 
⸻
 
1. Purpose
This document provides the operational procedures required to recover Production workloads into the Disaster Recovery (DR) environment hosted within Amazon Web Services (AWS).
The runbook establishes a repeatable recovery process for infrastructure, storage, identity services, databases, applications, load balancers, and end-user access components.
The goal is to ensure that recovered workloads can support business operations during a Disaster Recovery exercise or an actual Production outage.
This document is intended to be used by:
	•	Infrastructure Engineers
	•	Cloud Engineers
	•	Active Directory Administrators
	•	Storage Administrators
	•	Database Administrators
	•	Application Support Teams
	•	Disaster Recovery Coordinators
	•	Business Validation Teams
 
⸻
 
2. Scope
This runbook applies to systems hosted within:
	•	AWS Production Account
	•	AWS Disaster Recovery Account
The procedures documented within this manual support:
Disaster Recovery Exercises
Controlled recovery events executed for validation and testing purposes.
Planned Recovery Testing
Recovery activities executed to validate recovery procedures and recovery time objectives.
Actual Disaster Events
Recovery activities executed when Production services become unavailable and business services must be restored within the Disaster Recovery environment.
 
⸻
 
