	•	Application Access Endpoints
 
⸻
 
4. Active Directory Design
Domain Architecture
The Production and Disaster Recovery environments utilize the same Active Directory domain.
Example:
corp.company.com
The Domain Controllers used within the Disaster Recovery environment are replicated or recovered from Production and provide authentication services for recovered workloads.
 
⸻
 
Hostname Retention
Recovered servers retain the hostname present at the time of replication.
Example:
Production
APP01

Recovered DR
APP01
This behavior is expected.
Hostname retention is not considered a failure condition.
 
⸻
 
Important Clarification
The purpose of the domain integration process is not to rename recovered servers.
The purpose is to:
	•	Validate Active Directory connectivity
	•	Validate DNS functionality
	•	Establish or repair trust relationships
	•	Validate authentication services
	•	Validate secure channel operations
Authoritative validation methods include:
Test-ComputerSecureChannel
and
nltest /dsgetdc:corp.company.com
 
⸻
 
5. Recovery Philosophy
A common failure during Disaster Recovery exercises occurs when application recovery begins before foundational services have been validated.
Examples include:
	•	Domain Join Failures
	•	Authentication Failures
	•	DNS Failures
	•	FSx Access Failures
	•	Database Startup Failures
	•	Application Startup Failures
To avoid these conditions, all recovery activities must follow the approved dependency model.
 
⸻
 
6. Recovery Dependency Model
Recovery activities must follow the sequence below.
Domain Controllers
        ↓
DNS Services
        ↓
FSx
        ↓
Database Servers
        ↓
Application Servers
        ↓
Web Servers
        ↓
Target Groups
        ↓
Load Balancers
        ↓
Application Validation
        ↓
DR WorkSpace Validation
        ↓
Business Acceptance
No phase may begin until the previous phase has been successfully completed.
 
⸻
 
7. Recovery Priority Matrix
Priority	Component	Dependency
1	Domain Controllers	None
2	DNS Services	Domain Controllers
3	FSx	DNS + AD
4	Database Servers	DNS + AD + FSx
5	Application Servers	Databases
6	Web Servers	Applications
7	Target Groups	Applications
8	ALB / NLB	Target Groups
9	DR WorkSpaces	Entire Stack
 
