9. DR Readiness Validation
Objective
Validate that the Disaster Recovery environment is capable of supporting recovered workloads before recovery activities begin.
This phase prevents infrastructure recovery from starting before foundational services are available.
 
⸻
 
Why This Matters
Many failed Disaster Recovery exercises occur because infrastructure recovery begins before:
	•	Active Directory is operational
	•	DNS is operational
	•	Systems Manager is operational
	•	FSx is operational
Validating these services before recovery significantly reduces troubleshooting effort later in the recovery process.
 
⸻
 
10. AWS Infrastructure Validation
Objective
Validate AWS services required to support recovery activities.
 
⸻
 
Validation Checklist
Verify access to:
	•	EC2
	•	Systems Manager
	•	FSx
	•	Route53
	•	Secrets Manager
	•	Load Balancers
	•	CloudWatch
	•	IAM
 
⸻
 
Evidence Required
Capture screenshots showing:
	•	Successful console access
	•	Account access
	•	IAM access
Store all evidence in the DR Exercise Repository.
 
⸻
 
11. Active Directory Readiness Validation
Objective
Validate that Domain Controllers are operational before workload recovery begins.
 
⸻
 
Execution Location
Execute from:
	•	DR Domain Controller
	•	DR Management Server
	•	Active Directory Administration Host
Do not execute these validations from recovered application servers.
 
⸻
 
Validation Procedure
nltest /dclist:corp.company.com
 
⸻
 
Expected Result
List of Domain Controllers Returned
 
⸻
 
Evidence Required
Capture:
