22. Active Directory Connectivity Validation
Objective
Validate communication between recovered infrastructure and the Disaster Recovery Domain Controllers before executing domain integration procedures.
This phase serves as the final validation checkpoint before Active Directory trust remediation and domain integration activities begin.
 
⸻
 
Background
Many domain integration failures are incorrectly attributed to:
	•	Active Directory
	•	Credentials
	•	SSM Documents
In reality, most failures are caused by:
	•	DNS failures
	•	Security Group restrictions
	•	Network ACL restrictions
	•	Route table issues
	•	Domain Controller reachability failures
Connectivity validation isolates infrastructure problems before domain integration begins.
 
⸻
 
Dependencies
Before beginning this phase:
	•	Domain Controllers validated
	•	DNS validated
	•	FSx validated
	•	Network validation completed
	•	Application infrastructure recovered
 
⸻
 
Important Validation Requirement
All tests within this section must be executed from the recovered server itself.
Do not execute these tests from:
	•	Administrator laptops
	•	Bastion hosts
	•	Jump servers
	•	DR WorkSpaces
The objective is to validate connectivity from the recovered system.
 
⸻
 
Required Active Directory Ports
Service	Port	Purpose
DNS	53	Name Resolution
Kerberos	88	Authentication
RPC Endpoint Mapper	135	AD Communications
LDAP	389	Directory Queries
SMB	445	SYSVOL / NETLOGON
LDAPS	636	Secure LDAP
Global Catalog	3268	Forest Queries
Global Catalog SSL	3269	Secure Forest Queries
 
⸻
 
