37. Failure Handling Framework
Objective
Provide a structured methodology for handling failures encountered during Disaster Recovery exercises and actual disaster events.
This framework ensures failures are:
	•	Identified consistently
	•	Escalated appropriately
	•	Remediated efficiently
	•	Documented completely
 
⸻
 
Background
A common mistake during Disaster Recovery exercises is attempting to continue recovery activities despite unresolved foundational issues.
Examples:
	•	Continuing application recovery while DNS is broken
	•	Continuing domain integration while Domain Controllers are unavailable
	•	Continuing user testing while FSx is inaccessible
This frequently causes:
	•	False failures
	•	Extended recovery times
	•	Misleading exercise results
The objective of this framework is to isolate issues before they impact additional recovery phases.
 
