# 62. AWS Elastic Disaster Recovery (DRS) Recovery Operations

## Objective

Recover protected Production servers into the Disaster Recovery environment using AWS Elastic Disaster Recovery (DRS).

This section provides the operational procedures for launching recovered instances and validating successful recovery.

---

## Background

AWS DRS continuously replicates Production workloads into a staging area.

During a recovery event:

- Recovery instances are launched
- Volumes are recreated
- Network mappings applied
- Security Groups assigned
- Workloads brought online

Recovery success does not automatically imply application readiness.

Post-recovery validation is required.

---

# Recovery Workflow

```text
Production Server
        ↓
Continuous Replication
        ↓
AWS DRS
        ↓
Launch Recovery Instance
        ↓
Recover into DR
        ↓
Validate Infrastructure
        ↓
Validate Applications
```

---

